{"comments":"Temporal Integrity — Big Δt and little δt.\n\nAfter Thomas Campbell's \"My Big TOE\":\n\n- Δt (InfraTime): Infrastructural time. Real wall-clock seconds.\n  The tick rate of reality itself. Cannot be manipulated.\n\n- δt (ExperientialTime): Experiential time. Subjective seconds within\n  the game. Can vary (slow-mo, time-skip) but is BOUNDED.\n\n## The Security Invariant\n\nExperientialTime ≤ maxTimeRatio × InfraTime\n\nNo experience can create subjective time exceeding K times real time.\nThis prevents:\n- Torture loops (1 second feels like 1000 years)\n- Time theft (stealing compute by running fast)\n- Temporal isolation (entity experiences eons alone)\n\n## Implementation\n\nThe tick function MUST receive trusted infrastructure time.\nBefore processing a tick, it checks if the proposed experiential delta\nwould exceed the temporal budget. If so, it rejects the tick.\n\nThis is ENFORCEMENT, not just tracking.\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Maximum ratio of experiential to infrastructural time.\n\nK = 10 means: for every 1 real second, at most 10 experiential seconds.\n\nThis is the CONSTITUTIONAL CONSTANT that prevents torture loops.\nChanging this value has profound security implications.\n\nRationale for K=10:\n- Allows 10× time acceleration (fast-forward, time-skip)\n- 1 real hour → max 10 experiential hours\n- 1 real day → max 10 experiential days\n- Still bounded: 1 real second cannot feel like 1000 years\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[120,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Game/Temporal.purs","start":[120,1]},"title":"maxTimeRatio"},{"children":[],"comments":"Maximum experiential time per individual tick (seconds).\n\nEven within budget, a single tick cannot advance more than this.\nThis prevents \"time bomb\" ticks that dump huge deltas.\n\nSet to 1.0 second — same as DeltaTime bound in Entity.purs.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[129,33],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Game/Temporal.purs","start":[129,1]},"title":"maxExperientialPerTick"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Game","Temporal"],"InfraTime"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[145,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Game/Temporal.purs","start":[145,1]},"title":"eqInfraTime"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Game","Temporal"],"InfraTime"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[146,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Game/Temporal.purs","start":[146,1]},"title":"ordInfraTime"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Game","Temporal"],"InfraTime"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[149,55],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Game/Temporal.purs","start":[148,1]},"title":"showInfraTime"}],"comments":"Infrastructure time in seconds.\n\nThis is REAL wall-clock time. It comes from the runtime, not from\ngame logic. It cannot be manipulated by game code.\n\nBounded: 0 to 1e12 seconds (~31,700 years).\nThis allows long-running simulations while preventing overflow.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[143,37],"name":"../../hy